                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4094: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-25T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 25, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. Your 53, June 25, 11 a.m. Belgium is of course one of the important countries
                    included in the President’s proposal. It has been repeatedly and clearly told
                    the Belgian Ambassador that Belgium is one of the important creditor powers and
                    the Ambassador said he would so inform his Government. Belgium stands to lose
                    all of their conditional payments if a moratorium is declared by Germany. She
                    has more to lose in case a debacle occurs in Germany than any other nation.</p>
                <p>Please transmit the above information orally to the Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
